I '''Nathaniel Borenstein''' (mibait  [[Septiembri 23]], [[1957]]) metung ya kareng menimunang designer na ning [[MIME]] protocolpara balangkasan ne ing multimedia [[Internet]] [[E-mail|electronic mail]].<ref>[http://www.guppylake.com/~nsb/Nathaniel.html Nathaniel S. Borenstein's CV]</ref>

Kasalungsungan Hepi ning Open Standards Strategist ampong Kilalang Engineer king [[IBM]], i Borenstein iya ing mitatag keng  NetPOS.com<ref>[http://www.netpos.com NetPOS.com web site]</ref> ampong ing [[First Virtual|First Virtual Holdings]], a ausan dang  "ing mumunang cyberbank" na ning [[Smithsonian Institution]]. Ikua ne ing kayang [[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]] keng [[Mathematicu]] ampo ing kayang [[Pamagaral Pangkasalpantayanan (Religious Studies)]] ibat king [[Grinnell College]], kabang ikua ne ing [[M.S.]] ampong [[Ph.D]] iabt king [[Carnegie Mellon University]].  Megaral ya naman king [[Deep Springs College]], [[California]] (1975-76), [[Ohio State University]] (1974-75), ampo king [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]], [[Israel]] (1978-79).

Iya ing sinualt keng ''Programming As If People Mattered: Friendly Programs, Software Engineering, and Other Noble Delusions'' (Princeton University Press, 1994) ISBN 0691037639.


